Package lgp.core.program.registers

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Argument<T>
    An class Argument is essentially just the value of a particular class Register, but in the context of an lgp.core.evolution.instructions.Operation.
    Arguments<T>
    A simple collection of class Arguments.
    RandomRegisterGenerator<T>
    Generates an infinite random sequence of registers from the register set given.
    Register<T>
    A register that is available to an LGP program.
    RegisterSet<T>
    Represents a collection of class Registers.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    RegisterType
    Represents the type of a register.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    RegisterAccessException
    Thrown when a write operation is attempted on a RegisterType.Constant register.
    RegisterWriteRangeException
    Thrown when the number of values being written to a particular register range, does not match the size of the range.
